couple of large tomatoes, and a bunch of bananas. And if you agree to show me your ‘finished product,’ there will be another treat: I promise to divulge to you why I gave you, or rather who gave you, your theme.”

“What theme?” said Shade absently, as he leaned on my arm and gradually recovered the use of his numb limb.

“Our blue inenubilable Zembla, and the red-capped Steinmann, and the motorboat in the sea cave, and—”

“Ah,” said Shade, “I think I guessed your secret qui